@startuml "Terminal State and Buffer Components"
title "Terminal State Management with SRP Buffer Separation"

' ==================== TERMINAL STATE ====================

package "Terminal State" {
  class TerminalState {
    + output: OutputBuffer
    + input: InputBuffer
    + history: CommandHistory
    + mode: TerminalMode
    + pending_interaction: Option<PendingInteraction>
    - visible_lines: usize
    --
    + new(): Self
    --
    + add_output(line): void
    + add_output_lines(lines): void
    + clear_input(): void
    + submit_input(): String
    + insert_char(c): void
    + delete_char(): void
    + move_cursor_left(): void
    + move_cursor_right(): void
    + history_previous(): void
    + history_next(): void
    + scroll_up(): void
    + scroll_down(): void
    + set_visible_lines(lines): void
    + visible_lines() -> usize
  }

  note right of TerminalState
    **Single Responsibility**
    Composes specialized buffers
    Delegates to appropriate buffer

    **State Composition**
    - OutputBuffer: Display buffer with scrolling
    - InputBuffer: Cursor-aware input line
    - CommandHistory: Command history navigation
    - TerminalMode: Current mode tracking
    - visible_lines: Terminal viewport height

    **Mode Enum**
    - Normal: Waiting for input
    - ExecutingCommand: Running shell command
    - WaitingLLM: Querying LLM
    - PromptingInstall: M2/M3 auto-install (reserved)
    - AwaitingCommandApproval: HITL approval (y/n)
    - AwaitingAnswer: HITL free-form answer

    **Visible Lines Management**
    - Updated during render()
    - Used for scroll calculations
    - Passed to OutputBuffer::scroll_down()
  end note
}

' ==================== OUTPUT BUFFER ====================

package "Output Buffer" {
  class OutputBuffer {
    - buffer: Vec<String>
    - scroll_position: usize
    --
    + new(): Self
    + add_line(line): void
    + add_lines(lines): void
    + clear(): void
    + lines(): &[String]
    + scroll_position() -> usize
    + scroll_up(): void
    + scroll_down(visible_lines): void
    + set_visible_lines(visible_lines): void
    + pop(): Option<String>
  }

  note right of OutputBuffer
    **Responsibilities**
    - Manages display output buffer
    - Scrolling support (up/down)
    - Auto-scroll to bottom on new output
    - Memory management with trimming

    **Scrolling Implementation**
    - scroll_up(): Move view up 1 line
    - scroll_down(visible_lines): Scroll down with bounds check
    - set_visible_lines(): Clamp position on resize
    - auto_scroll_to_bottom(): Smart scroll on new content

    **Performance**
    - Append: O(1) amortized
    - Scroll: O(1)
    - Trim: O(n) where n = trimmed lines

    **Memory Management**
    - MAX_OUTPUT_LINES: 10,000
    - TRIM_LINES: 1,000 (headroom on trim)
    - Scroll position adjusted on trim
    - Auto-scroll to latest content
  end note
}

' ==================== INPUT BUFFER ====================

package "Input Buffer" {
  class InputBuffer {
    - buffer: String
    - cursor_pos: usize
    --
    + new(): Self
    + clear(): void
    + insert_char(c): void
    + delete_char(): void
    + set_text(text): void
    + take(): String
    + move_cursor_left(): void
    + move_cursor_right(): void
    + current(): &str
    + cursor_position(): usize
  }

  note right of InputBuffer
    **Responsibilities**
    - Manages user input line
    - Cursor position tracking
    - Character insertion/deletion
    - Text replacement

    **Performance**
    - Insert: O(n) where n = text length
    - Delete: O(n)
    - Cursor movement: O(1)

    **Cursor Tracking**
    - Position: 0 to buffer.len()
    - Move left/right: 1 position
    - Prevents out-of-bounds
  end note
}

' ==================== COMMAND HISTORY ====================

package "Command History" {
  class CommandHistory {
    - entries: Vec<String>
    - position: usize
    --
    + new(): Self
    + add(command): void
    + all(): &[String]
    + previous(): Option<String>
    + next(): Option<String>
    + reset_position(): void
  }

  note right of CommandHistory
    **Responsibilities**
    - Stores command history
    - Navigation (previous/next)
    - Position tracking

    **Semantics**
    - get-second-to-last: History already
      contains current input when classified
    - previous(): Move back one entry
    - next(): Move forward one entry
    - reset_position(): Go to end (after submit)

    **History Expansion Integration**
    - HistoryExpansionHandler accesses via
      Arc<RwLock<Vec<String>>>
    - Patterns: !!, !$, !^, !*
    - Synchronized in InfrawareTerminal
    - Updated on each submit_input()

    **Session-Only** (M1)
    - Not persisted to disk
    - Lost on terminal exit
    - M2: Persist to ~/.infraware_history
  end note
}

' ==================== EVENT HANDLING ====================

package "Terminal Events" {
  enum TerminalEvent {
    Quit
    InputChar(char)
    DeleteChar
    MoveCursorLeft
    MoveCursorRight
    HistoryPrevious
    HistoryNext
    ScrollUp
    ScrollDown
    Submit
    TabComplete
    ClearScreen
    CtrlC
    Resize(u16, u16)
    Unknown
  }

  class EventHandler {
    --
    + new(): Self
    + poll_event(timeout): Result<Option<TerminalEvent>>
    - map_event(event): TerminalEvent
    - map_key_event(key): TerminalEvent
  }

  note right of EventHandler
    **Responsibilities**
    - Poll keyboard/resize events
    - Translate to TerminalEvent
    - Handle Windows quirks

    **Keyboard Event Translation**
    - Key::Char(c) → InputChar
    - Key::Backspace → DeleteChar
    - Key::Left → MoveCursorLeft
    - Key::Right → MoveCursorRight
    - Key::Up (no mod) → HistoryPrevious
    - Key::Down (no mod) → HistoryNext
    - Key::Up + Ctrl → ScrollUp
    - Key::Down + Ctrl → ScrollDown
    - Key::PageUp → ScrollUp
    - Key::PageDown → ScrollDown
    - Key::Tab → TabComplete
    - Key::Enter → Submit
    - Ctrl+L → ClearScreen
    - Ctrl+C → CtrlC

    **Windows-Specific**
    - Filter KeyEventKind::Press only
    - Ignore Repeat/Release events
    - Prevents duplicate processing
  end note

  class TerminalMode <<enum>> {
    Normal
    ExecutingCommand
    WaitingLLM
    PromptingInstall
  }
}

' ==================== TUI RENDERING ====================

package "TUI Rendering" {
  class TerminalUI {
    - terminal: Terminal<CrosstermBackend>
    --
    + new(): Result<Self>
    + render(&mut state): Result<()>
    + clear(): Result<()>
    + suspend(): Result<()>
    + resume(): Result<()>
    + cleanup(): Result<()>
    + inner_terminal(): &mut Terminal
  }

  note right of TerminalUI
    **Responsibilities**
    - Ratatui rendering
    - Raw mode management
    - Alternate screen handling
    - Interactive command suspension
    - Visible lines calculation

    **Render Process**
    1. Calculate visible lines from terminal size
    2. Call state.set_visible_lines(lines)
    3. Render frame using state
    4. Scrolling uses visible_lines value

    **Render Layout**
    - Header: banner + mode indicator
    - Output: scrollable display area
    - Input: user input line
    - Cursor: blinking at input position
    - Scrollbar: visual indicator

    **Interactive Command Flow**
    1. suspend(): Leave TUI mode
    2. Command runs in normal terminal
    3. resume(): Re-enter TUI mode
    4. Screen repainted

    **Error Handling**
    - Panic-safe via RAII (TuiGuard)
    - Cleanup on exit guaranteed
    - Raw mode disabled safely

    **Mutable State Parameter**
    - Signature: render(&mut TerminalState)
    - Updates visible_lines during render
    - Allows OutputBuffer sync
  end note
}

' ==================== SPLASH SCREEN ====================

package "Splash Screen" {
  class SplashScreen {
    + run(terminal): Result<()>
    - animate_particles(): async Result<()>
  }

  note right of SplashScreen
    **5-Second Animated Intro**
    - Particle assembly effect
    - 5 second duration
    - Skippable with Enter/Escape
    - Runs before main event loop
  end note
}

' Relationships
TerminalState --> OutputBuffer : owns
TerminalState --> InputBuffer : owns
TerminalState --> CommandHistory : owns
TerminalState --> TerminalMode : tracks
EventHandler --> TerminalEvent : generates
TerminalUI --> TerminalState : renders
CommandHistory --> "Arc<RwLock>" : synced with history_arc
EventHandler --> "crossterm" : uses for events
TerminalUI --> "ratatui" : uses for rendering

' Data flow
note top
  **Data Flow with Scrolling**

  EventHandler polls events
         ↓
  TerminalEvent (e.g., ScrollUp, ScrollDown, CtrlUp, CtrlDown)
         ↓
  InfrawareTerminal::handle_event()
         ↓
  Updates TerminalState buffer/history/scroll
         ↓
  TerminalUI::render(&mut state)
         ├─ Calculates visible_lines from terminal size
         ├─ Calls state.set_visible_lines(lines)
         └─ Renders with updated state
         ↓
  Event loop repeats

  **Scrolling Implementation**
  - Keyboard Events: Ctrl+Up/Down or PageUp/Down → ScrollUp/Down
  - Handler: InfrawareTerminal calls state.scroll_up/down()
  - TerminalState: Delegates to OutputBuffer.scroll_down(visible_lines)
  - OutputBuffer: Uses visible_lines for bounds checking
  - Render: Updates visible_lines from terminal size

  **History Expansion Sync**
  - HistoryExpansionHandler uses Arc<RwLock>
  - Updated in handle_submit()
  - Lock contention: minimal (submit only)
  - Poisoning recovery: in place
end note

@enduml
